snippet.title: Yale Real Living Touchscreen Z-Wave Deadbolt
snippet.description: If you're looking for a higher level of convenience from your lock, but you don't want to pay monthly fees, then you'll want to give this deadbolt your consideration.

snippet.title: 2015 Ford Focus
snippet.description: Ford's chosen to unveil it's new compact at Mobile World Congress, a week ahead of the big auto show in Geneva. It packs better tech inside, new driver aids, and a subtly revised exterior.

snippet.title: Real Racing 3
snippet.description: Even with the freemium model, Real Racing 3 still holds the crown as best racing game on a touch screen.

snippet.title: Samsung KN55F9500 Real OLED TV
snippet.description: After a false start in 2012, Samsung shows it's getting serious about OLED technology by announcing another 55-inch set, the N55F9500 Real OLED TV.

snippet.title: KitchenAid 5-Speed Diamond Blender Review
snippet.description: If you're looking for a blender that can multitask and do more than just make smoothies, but don't want to shell out a lot of money, the KitchenAid 5-Speed Diamond Blender is a great option.

snippet.title: Barcelona braces for Mobile World Congress (pictures)
snippet.description: The massive trade show devoted to mobile phones and networks doesn't officially start until Monday, but preparations are under way as the tech world descends on this Catalonian city.

snippet.title: Blackberry Q20
snippet.description: A fresh keyboard phone, the BlackBerry Q20 becomes a reality at MWC 2014.

snippet.title: Mozilla's $25 Firefox OS: It's real, and it works
snippet.description: Relatively affluent people will shun this smartphone. But for people who can afford only a bargain-priced feature phone, Mozilla's prototype shows promise.
